#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code har index par kitna water trap hoga, ye left max aur right max ki help se nikalta hai.

1. left[i] me i tak ka maximum height store kiya gaya hai.
   Matlab current index ke left side ki highest wall.
2. right[i] me i se end tak ka maximum height store kiya gaya hai.
   Matlab current index ke right side ki highest wall.
3. Ab har index par water store hoga:
   min(left[i], right[i]) - height[i]
4. Is value ko sab indices ke liye add karke total trapped water nikal lete hain.

Main idea:
Kisi bhi position par paani utna hi ruk sakta hai
jitni chhoti wall left max aur right max me se hogi.

Important:
- left max boundary batata hai
- right max boundary batata hai
- current height hataane par actual trapped water milta hai

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int trap(int[] height) {

        int n = height.length;
        int[] left = new int[n];
        int[] right = new int[n];
        //left
        left[0] = height[0];
        for(int i=1; i<n; i++){
            left[i] = Math.max(left[i-1], height[i]);
        }

        right[n-1] = height[n-1];
        //Right
        for(int i=n-2; i>=0; i--){
            right[i] = Math.max(right[i+1], height[i]);
        }

        int total = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            total += Math.min(left[i], right[i]) - height[i];
        }

        return total;
        
    }
}
